article.story: DAYTON, Ohio -- — Enoch Cheeks scored 23 points as Dayton beat Ball State 77-69 on Wednesday night. Cheeks had 12 rebounds and three steals for the Flyers (3-0). Malachi Smith scored 17 points while shooting 5 of 6 from the field and 5 for 6 from the line and added six rebounds, 10 assists, and three steals. Zed Key shot 4 of 5 from the field and 5 for 6 from the line to finish with 13 points. The Cardinals (1-2) were led by Jermahri Hill, who posted 25 points and seven rebounds. Ethan Brittain-Watts added 16 points for Ball State. Mickey Pearson Jr. also put up 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
